# Fix "jpackage.exe is missing" when Gradle uses Android Studio JBR (not a full JDK).
#
# 1. Install JDK 17: https://adoptium.net/ (Eclipse Temurin).
# 2. Copy this file to `gradle.properties` in this folder.
# 3. Set the path (forward slashes work on Windows).
#
# If you also set org.gradle.java.home in %USERPROFILE%\.gradle\gradle.properties (e.g. to Studio JBR
# for Android), that file wins over this one. On Windows, run `package-msi.cmd` instead of plain
# gradlew packageMsi — it uses a local Gradle home so this path is honored.
#
# org.gradle.java.home=C:/Program Files/Eclipse Adoptium/jdk-17.0.18.8-hotspot
#
# 4. package-msi.cmd   (recommended on Windows if ~/.gradle sets java.home)
#    — or: gradlew.bat --stop && gradlew.bat packageMsi
# WiX: optional on PATH; Compose can download WiX (see build log).
